bahrain princess married u . s . soldier shocked by death
the king of bahrain , who married johnson , a us marine soldier , has been widely praised by a us television station . however , this tortuous marriage has been going on for five years and has now ended in las vegas , a gambling city in the desert .
as a member of the royal family of bahrain in the gulf country , johnson took the risk of losing his military career , and his marriage was like a fairy tale , and became the theme of a tv movie .
however , according to the las vegas commentary , it took only five years for the two to file a lawsuit against the court , and mei lian filed a divorce , and the place was a gambling city with a faster marriage .
the two met in 1999 when johnson and a professional soldier were stationed in bahrain .
after he came to know this little princess in his prime of life , there was a great change in his life .
because the royal family banned the integration of the two little lovers , she was born in the name of mei lian , and she was allowed to put on her clothes , put on a baseball hat , and gave her a false military document , and secretly brought her out of the motherland and arrived in the united states .
after a hard - working immigration lawsuit with the us authorities , the young couple finally married in the candle light marriage church on the famous las vegas avenue , where the 23 - year - old johnson and the new girl were only 19 years old .
however , johnson said that because of the many temptations in las vegas , which is called " a city of crime , " he has been in a tense relationship with the parents ' home of merlian , a big financial power , and there is a rumor that there is a plot to assassinate him . this tortuous marriage is finally unable to sustain .
johnson said that he had to stop for the guests of the hotel and gambling house , and meili gradually got into the night life of the gambling city , and often went to the night shop and did not keep his husband in the eye .
mei li an abandoned her husband a year ago .
johnson said , " she has reached the end . "
euro zone 's economic indicators this week will show continued weak european economy
economists said that the economic indicators to be released this week in the euro zone will show further evidence of weak economic confidence and slowing down economic output , while british data are expected to show an increase in industrial activities .
they said that the economic output data of the largest euro zone country would continue to show great fluctuations every month , but the long - term trend of economic output would indicate a slowdown in economic growth .
the most important economic indicators for this week will provide evidence of the first economic confidence in europe in december , which is expected to be released on the 7 th in germany .
in november , the ump dropped sharply from 31.3 percent in the previous month to 13.9 percent .
economists said that the sharp appreciation of the euro will continue to have an impact on economic confidence in a recent survey , so there is no reason to expect the economic indicators to rebound .
" taking into account the main factors leading to the decline in economic confidence , including the appreciation of the euro , the uncertainties in the global economy , and the worsening unemployment rate in the german employment market , all have a negative impact on the future growth forecast during the december survey , so it is impossible for the strong rebound in the index . "
according to a survey conducted by afp 's financial news , the index will drop again to 11 in december from 13.9 in the previous month .
however , he said that the projected economic indicators for germany 's economy , in december , might even fall to zero .
" according to our view , the future prospects of germany 's economic activities will continue to decline , as reflected by the survey conducted by the government on analysts and financial market participants , " he said .
tense situation in ukraine to become osce 's agenda
russia has repeatedly accused the west of interfering in east european affairs because the political crisis in ukraine has become a focus of attention , and the annual meeting of ministers of the organization for security and cooperation in europe to be held tomorrow will become a major topic .
western forces have gradually extended into the corner of europe , which was originally regarded by russia as its backyard , such as the baltic sea countries , georgia , and central asia , and russia has long been quite dissatisfied . therefore , when the organization for security and cooperation in europe held a two - day meeting in sofia , capital of bulgaria , the recent incident in ukraine may become an important topic .
the ukrainian supreme court has made a dramatic ruling to order the second round of voting in the recent presidential election . before that , the european union had called on the member states of the organization for security and cooperation in europe to prepare the observers to " take action at the fastest speed and efficiency . "
the number of observers sent by the organization for security and cooperation in europe ( osce ) may increase from 600 to 1,000 in the re - election scheduled for december 26 , european sources said .
us secretary of state colin powell will attend the annual meeting of the organization for security and cooperation in europe ( osce ) , which may be his last visit before leaving office .
russian foreign minister lavrov , french foreign minister barnier , british foreign minister straw , and german foreign minister fischer will also attend the meeting .
members of the organization for security and cooperation in europe , including 55 countries in north america , europe , and asia , will celebrate the 30th anniversary of its founding next year .
the organization was set up in helsinki at that time and has contributed to the end of the cold war .
bush 's major test of intelligence reform bill faces congress vote this week
the us congress , which will go all out to pass the intelligence reform bill this week , is the republican president bush 's ambitious plan for the second term , and his support for republican congressmen is the first time he is facing a major test after he is re - elected .
former republican new jersey governor keane , who was responsible for investigating the september 11 , 2001 terrorist attacks on new york and washington , said in a newspaper interview yesterday that the issue of the intelligence reform bill was to be passed by the congress , and that this alone was a bad sign of future cooperation between the two parties and the president 's domestic policy agenda .
" if the president and the congress fail to handle these major issues well , the congress will become ineffective , and we will have trouble , " keane said .
he told the daily news in new york : " we have been waiting for a long time to have another bill that can win the support of the republican and democratic leaders of the senate and the house of representatives , and 80 percent of the popular support . "
many congressmen said yesterday that if the historic reform bill fails , it will delay the thorough maintenance of the old us spy network system for several months , or even several years , or even completely damage its existence .
" if this bill is not passed this week , it will die in the bud , " said haman , chief democrat member of the house intelligence committee , on cnn yesterday .
the congress will try to pass the " intelligence reform and terrorist prevention and control bill 2004 " again on the 6 th and 7 th , and will be adjourned to early next year .
if the bill is not passed , it will become invalid and will not be redrafted until 2005 .
ukraine 's opposition refuses to give up president 's power to revise constitution
ukraine 's pro - western opposition parties insisted today that they would not accept the constitutional reform that will be carried out before the second round of the presidential election .
the constitutional reform will deprive the majority of the current president 's power .
after the second round of voting by the supreme court was full of flaws , the november 21 election was invalid , and the central election commission ordered the re - election on december 26 , the opposition leader viktor chernomyrdin was in a stalemate again .
" if the constitutional amendment is passed in the current form , all the power of the president will be transferred to the parliament , and this is unacceptable , " said the president 's ally , the president .
she told reporters : " we hope that the president will be able to appoint intelligence bureau chief and chief procurator , so that we can fight corruption and remove the group that controls the political and commercial industries in ukraine . "
kuchema , who has maintained close ties with russia , is pushing for constitutional amendment before the election because he is worried that the opposition may win the presidential election .
the opposition congressmen yesterday refused to vote on the constitutional amendment proposed by the government , and the congress was adjourned for 10 days .
according to the constitutional amendment , apart from the prime minister , the defense minister , and the foreign minister , the power of appointment of all heads of state will be transferred from the president to the parliament , and the forces that support the government now have a close majority of seats in the congress .
according to the content of the amendment , the prime minister , defense minister , and foreign minister appointed by the president must be approved by the congress , and the congress can also put forward their candidates .
ukraine 's political crisis enters third week
ukraine 's opposition leader viktor chernomyrdin today called for the support of the people to continue to protest in the streets , surrounded the presidential palace and the government building , until the soon - to - be - relieved president kujkovic and his cabinet members were removed , and actions were taken to ensure the fairness of the upcoming presidential election .
tens of thousands of supporters have gathered in the capital kiev for two weeks , and they surrounded the government building , sleeping the main road designed by soviet experts for the military parade . the people 's strength they displayed forced the supreme court to announce that the second round of the presidential election on november 21 was invalid . the central election commission has ordered the election to be held on december 26 . the parliament has approved the reform of the parliament , but the government has not yet signed an administrative order to replace the one of his successor .
the prime minister told the supporters who gathered in the capital 's independence square tonight that kuchema should replace his government , reorganize the central election commission , and both the parliament and kuchema should agree to amend the election law to prevent the election fraud .
" before these decisions are made , we cannot talk about lifting the siege of the government building or the presidential palace , " he said in his speech , which started on december 26 .
in the past 14 days , the square has demonstrated its love for ukraine and the citizens ' awareness of millions of ukrainian people who can defend their choice . "
he said : " we are experiencing a struggle between good and evil forces . the whole world is applauded for our victory , and the whole world is proud of ukraine . "
at a time when the opposition parties are stepping up pressure on the ruling authorities supported by moscow , viktor chernomyrdin and kuchema are once again bogged down in a stalemate in constitutional reform , polish president kwasniewski , lithuania 's president yavarov , and russia 's special envoy gelizlov are scheduled to arrive in kiev on the 6 th for another round of mediation .
egypt announces breakthrough in middle east peace process
egypt said that the middle east peace agreement is expected to have a new framework .
it also said that in the near future , it may send new ambassadors back to israel to resume the comprehensive diplomatic relations that have been suspended for four years .
the egyptian state - run middle east news agency quoted " high - level " egyptian sources as saying that the parties seeking a peace plan have gradually reached a consensus on a comprehensive reconciliation .
the middle east news agency said : " egypt , israel , palestine , and important international organizations , such as the united states and the european union , have reached an important understanding and agreed in principle to fully resolve the conflicts between israel and palestine . "
since the death of palestinian strong arafat last month , the international community has continued to promote the restoration of the middle east peace policy , with a view to ending the bloody conflicts between israel and palestine for many years at an early date .
the middle east news agency said that officials predicted that " preparatory work will be carried out in july and then political action will be taken . "
the middle east news agency said that after that , all parties concerned about the middle east peace process , israel and palestine , as well as egypt , the united states , russia , and several european countries will hold a meeting in washington .
it is expected that the meeting will include a " cease - fire between the two sides , " and the palestinian authorities will " stop anti - israeli attacks and strengthen its control over the gaza strip and the west bank . "
regarding this , the middle east news agency said that israeli prime minister sharon promised that " as long as the palestinian authorities respect the cease - fire agreement and control their places , israel will stop military actions against the palestinians . "
more than 1 billion children in the world suffer from war - stricken aids
the united nations children 's fund ( unicef ) today pointed out in its annual report that more than 1 billion children , which account for half of the world 's children , have been trampled on by poverty , war , and aids .
the united nations children 's fund ( unicef ) said that children under the convention on the rights of children in 1989 have the right to health and to be protected by the environment for growth , which is often endangered , because the governments of various countries have failed to implement human rights and economic reforms .
" when half of the children in the world grow up in a hunger and unhealthy environment , when schools become the target of attack , and when the whole village is destroyed by aids , we are unable to honor our commitment to children , " said the chairman of the executive committee of the united nations children 's fund in london .
" the governments of too many countries are making a deliberate choice that will actually harm children , " he added .
the statistics compiled by the united nations children 's fund ( unicef ) , in collaboration with researchers at the london institute of economics and the university of brisbane in the united kingdom , exposed the terrorist situation of children in most parts of the world .
researchers found that about 640 million children in the world were short of proper living places , 400 million children were unable to obtain safe drinking water , 270 million children were unable to enjoy health care services , and 140 million children ( most of them were girls ) had never studied .
researchers pointed out that more seriously , at least 700 million children suffered from various forms of " serious exploitation , " including being unable to get in touch with information and enjoying public health facilities .
the united nations children 's fund ( unicef ) said in its 10 th annual report today that wars and aids have destroyed all kinds of networks that can normally protect children , and children are often directly victims of war and aids .
china puts pressure on eu to lift arms embargo
the european union ( eu ) today rejected chinese premier wen jiabao , hoping to end the pressure on china 's arms embargo as soon as possible , but said it would work to lift the 15 - year embargo .
the eu 's rotating president , the netherlands , made the above remarks after the china - eu summit .
the netherlands said that there is no need for the eu to make improper speculation on how to stop the embargo .
the eu imposed arms embargo on beijing after the 1989 tiananmen massacre .
although the issue of arms embargo has cast a shadow on this china - eu summit , the two sides still signed a number of trade and other agreements at the meeting .
both china and the european union have claimed that these agreements have strengthened their " strategic partnership . "
in a joint statement issued after the summit meeting with chinese premier wen jiabao , the eu said : " the eu side confirms its political will to continue its efforts to lift the embargo . "
the statement pointed out that the chinese delegation " welcomes this positive message and believes that this message is beneficial to the healthy development of the broad strategic partnership between china and the eu . "
at a press conference after the summit , wen jiabao did not hide his unhappiness . he said that the embargo " failed to reflect the partnership between china and the eu . "
wen jiabao said : " this embargo is the result of the cold war , which cannot reflect the current situation , still less reflects the partnership between china and the eu . "
some eu countries , led by france , have pushed for the lifting of the arms embargo , claiming that the ban is outdated .
without revising and strengthening relevant eu laws , people of insight in the eu are worried that the lifting of the embargo may open up the flood prevention gate for arms sales and encourage china 's military strength .
" i explained that the european union is willing to lift the embargo , but i also pointed out that the lifting of the ban is related to the adjustment of the code of conduct for arms exports , " said dutch prime minister basknan .
initial study shows that acid may lead to breast cancer but there is no final conclusion
a latest health research report pointed out that the risk of breast cancer is rising because of the widespread use of vitamin b acid in order to prevent the fetus from deformities .
however , researchers said that their research results might only be accidental because other studies showed that the possibility of breast cancer would actually be reduced , so they called on pregnant women to continue to take this supplement .
acid naturally exists in dark - coloured leaf - type vegetables , and the medical profession is well aware that this is an important boost to the growth of foetus .
the researchers of the two universities in the united kingdom , the university of boulevard and the university of arbo , followed the 3,000 women , who had taken five mg of leaf acid or 0.2 mg of placenta when they were pregnant in the 1960 s , and most of them were the second and third stages of their pregnancy .
the report published in the british medical journal pointed out that as of september 2002 , the percentage of women who had taken five mg of ye acid was only two times that of those who had breast cancer .
one of the researchers stressed that this result is only " preliminary . " the purpose of the study is to point out the road of further study . "
he said : " it is entirely possible that this is a accidental result . therefore , before we reach any conclusion , we must carry out further scientific research to review the affiliated nature . if this kind of relationship exists . "
" women who plan to be pregnant are still advised to use acid to make up for the product , " he said .
he said that there is a considerable gap between the current dosage and the experimental dosage .
according to the british health standards , women who wish to be pregnant and in their first pregnancy should take 0.4 mg of acid per day , which is more than 10 times lower than the dosage taken by women in the above study .
two candidates in ukraine 's presidential election completely different
the two opponents who will meet in the presidential election in ukraine on the 26 th of this month are now ready to make a decision at a higher level .
the pro - western opposition leader viktor chernomyrdin is confident in winning the election , while the current pro - moscow prime minister yjinkovic said he will no longer represent the " shameful " ruling party to run for the election .
at the same time , russian president putin changed his attitude toward ukraine 's accession to the european union , saying he was pleased with ukraine 's entry into the european union .
when asked about his hope to win more than 20 percent of the votes in the re - election , viktor chernomyrdin told reporters at the press conference venue that " in conservative terms , i should get about 60 percent of the votes . "
on the other hand , it can be seen from the appearance that the jkovic , who is anxious and uneasy , has been able to avoid directly answering reporters ' questions on several occasions . in the end , he only said : " we will win if we are in the spirit of the emperor . "
yjinkovic , who had been nurtured by the current president kuchema as his successor , has now changed his course and defined himself as a candidate who opposes the opposition party and the ruling party .
he said in a way close to the direct name : " in the past , i trust those cosmos and scum who worked under the government , but now i am very disappointed , and this government is really ashamed . "
kuchema and the opposition parties exchanged conditions to transfer some of the president 's power to the parliament through the amendment of the law to end the two - week - long large - scale opposition and political chaos since the november 21 presidential election .
the former victory was also declared invalid by the supreme court on the grounds that the election process was running rampant , and the election must be re - elected .
powell 's last visit to the hague to try his best to maintain harmony between europe and the united states
us secretary of state colin powell held talks with high - level eu officials today , and for the last time in his term of office , he devoted his efforts to the unity between the united states and europe .
powell 's visit to europe is aimed at repairing the diplomatic damage caused by the iraq war to both sides , and the hague is the last stop of his visit .
powell 's visit may be his last official overseas visit during his term of office , and the eu promised to him that the eu will move toward the path of easing tension between the two sides before us president bush visits europe in february next year .
however , differences between the two sides still exist .
" we must strengthen bilateral dialogue during president bush 's second term of office and find a common position , " said the foreign minister of the netherlands , the rotating eu presidency .
the european commissioner for foreign affairs , ms. hua dena , said that she believed that europe and the united states had made some progress in " putting the iraq crisis in the face of difficulties , " but she also realized that the present is " a crucial moment in european - us relations . "
bush will fly to brussels on february 22 next year to meet with leaders of the european union and nato .
powell said that bush 's visit was aimed at repairing the cracks in relations caused by the iraq factor .
powell has visited sofia and brussels during his trip to europe , but the progress of improving relations is limited .
in particular , in brussels , powell criticized six nato countries that were opposed to the war for refusing to take part in the training mission in iraq , which has damaged the " reputation and unity " of the allies .
however , powell still insisted that his meeting had demonstrated the commitment of the united states to fully restore diplomatic relations .
