japan 's economic growth may slow down next year
as the appreciation of the japanese yen and the widening gap between the rich and the poor may undermine the harmonious atmosphere enjoyed in the first half of this year , the japanese economy may slow down and enter 2005 .
after 10 years of stagnation , high profits and strong consumer spending have enabled japan to regain confidence this year , but analysts have pointed their support for economic growth to china , despite the increasing political tension between japan and china .
the evidence has gradually shown that the japanese economy is likely to fall in a short period of time in early 2005 , especially if industrial production continues to decline , while manufacturers have adjusted their stocks to avoid overstock .
according to the new statistical method recently adopted , the japanese economy in the april - june quarter actually declined slightly , with a growth of only 0.1 percent in the july - september quarter , which has just avoided the technical recession .
at present , economists still hold very different views on the strength of japan 's economic rebound .
researchers from the bank of france estimated that japan 's real economic growth rate could reach 2.3 percent in the current fiscal year ending march next year and the next fiscal year .
they claimed that 2005 is the " recovery year " , and the reason is that the us economy has returned to the track of recovery steadily , and the japanese consumer spending has made up for the slowdown in exports .
another relatively pessimistic view is that the growth rate for the current fiscal year is only 1.8 percent , and the growth rate for the next fiscal year is even lower to 0.6 percent .
they quoted " potential risks " as saying that the profits of the manufacturers did not lead to an increase in personal income .
french fm : progress in middle east peace to test french - us relations
french foreign minister barnier said after meeting with us secretary of state powell today that the resumption of the middle east peace talks will " test " their relations across the atlantic ocean .
after the death of palestinian leader arafat , france called for holding an international symposium to promote the israeli - palestinian peace process , but there was no sign of reaching an agreement at the end of the meeting between barnier and powell .
barnier flew from paris to washington to attend a european union summit in brussels after a lightning meeting with powell and his designated national security adviser rice .
both paris and washington agreed to repair the tense relations between the two countries after the united states entered iraq last year , but the differences between the two countries in resolving the middle east deadlock remain obvious .
after a brief meeting between the us state department and powell , barnier said : " we hope to improve the future relations between france and the united states , as well as between europe and america . "
he said : " i think the test of the core relationship lies in our ability to promote the peace process between palestine and israel . "
barnier earlier this week called for an international middle east seminar at an early date to take advantage of the " opportunity window " he said after arafat died last month .
however , powell is still unwilling to make a commitment .
he said that the two talked about britain 's plan to hold a meeting attended by palestinians , but they did not mention whether to hold a more extensive international conference .
us officials have made it clear that their primary task is to promote peace in israel and palestine and ensure the smooth progress of the palestinian election next month .
the election will produce a leader who can control islamic militants and resume israel - palestine talks .
nobutaka kawaguchi proposes talks between japan and south korea next january
japan and south korea will start negotiations on the signing of a free trade agreement ( fta ) in january next year , japanese foreign minister nobutaka machimura said monday .
in a meeting with south korean minister of foreign affairs and trade ban ki - moon in the south of the island , nobutaka machimura said that both tokyo and seoul hoped to sign a free trade agreement by the end of 2005 , the two sides should resume negotiations as soon as possible .
prior to the talks with ban ki - moon , japanese prime minister junichiro koizumi and south korean president roh moo - hyun held a summit on the 17 th , during which roh moo - hyun urged tokyo authorities to be cautious on the issue of imposing economic sanctions on north korea .
north korea kidnapped a number of japanese citizens during the cold war , and prime minister koizumi is facing enormous pressure from the public to punish north korea .
after japanese researchers concluded last week that the remains provided by pyongyang authorities to prove that the two hostages had died were not the remains of the victims , they were very angry .
apart from the kidnapping issue , koizumi and roh moo - hyun agreed that the six - party talks aimed at preventing north korea from developing nuclear weapons should resume as soon as possible .
since north korea 's secret development of nuclear weapons triggered a confrontation in october 2002 , no concrete results have been achieved in the previous three rounds of six - party talks .
north korea later resisted the fourth round of six - party talks originally scheduled for september this year .
the six - party talks are south korea , north korea , the united states , china , japan and russia .
thai prime minister thaksin shinawatra still expected to win february elections
thai prime minister thaksin shinawatra is confident that he will be able to win the second four - year term in 2005 , but his reputation has been damaged because he has not been able to quell the bloody rebellion of the separatists .
thailand 's national general election is scheduled to be held on february 6 next year , and thaksin and his political rival are actively preparing for the election . most analysts believe that despite the serious violent clashes and bird flu outbreak in the southern part of the year , he is expected to win .
a total of 12 people in thailand died of avian flu this year , and the bird flu epidemic has swept across most parts of asia . however , in thailand , it is particularly serious . the thai government admitted that it was " wrong " in handling the epidemic .
however , the health problem is not likely to allow thaksin to remain in office , but on the contrary , many people are only asking what extent he will win , and what is the significance of his election to the muslim rebellion in the southern province ?
" the phenomenon here is that no matter how you look at dassin , he is now enjoying popular support . "
he said : " however , the situation will start to collapse next year . if you look at the accumulation of wealth ( his family and people around him ) , as well as the unfair and violent situation in society . "
it was precisely because of social unfairness and violence that turmoil broke out in the areas where the muslim majority in the southern part of thailand , and since the beginning of the month , isolated rebellion has occurred continuously .
since january this year , the islamic militants have regarded buddhism , government officials , and security forces as targets in the gunbattle , and they have also carried out bomb attacks and attacks . so far , more than 560 people have been killed and 100 others have been missing .
