bush admits training of iraqi troops needs to be strengthened , rumsfeld
us president bush admitted today that the iraqi troops have not been well prepared to replace the us military and warned that the general election scheduled to be held on january 30 next year will not be the end of a serious riot in iraq .
at a one - hour press conference , bush also expressed his support for secretary of defense rumsfeld and firmly believed that the pentagon chief " is good at doing his job . "
bush said that although there was a serious quarrel sometimes , he vowed to continue to cooperate with russian president putin and said it was time to move toward the end of the middle east conflict .
he also believes that the best way to deal with the issue of iraq and north korea , which are members of the " axis of evil , " is to resolve the issue through multi - national diplomacy .
