us navy helicopters flew to banda aceh , the capital of aceh province , today , and more and more field hospitals are operating in the city , and a large number of relief supplies are also arriving at the airport .
however , the head of the un office for the coordination of humanitarian affairs in indonesia , aimquster , told reporters that since there are many problems in coordination and infrastructure , it is impossible for relief supplies to be delivered quickly .
