japan offers 500 million u.s. dollars in disaster relief
japan today promised to provide 500 million us dollars in aid to countries affected by the indian ocean tsunami , and at a time when all countries are vying to help the victims of the world 's most serious disaster , japan 's aid has risen to the top of all countries , and has also increased the total amount of disaster relief and reconstruction funds promised by the international community to 1.6 billion us dollars .
japanese prime minister junichiro koizumi said in a statement that japan , as the largest economy in asia , will consider providing more aid , including money and technology .
he said : " japan will do its best to provide assistance in three aspects : financial resources , knowledge technology , and human resources . "
he said : " japan will temporarily give a donation of 500 million us dollars to disaster - stricken countries and relevant international organizations as emergency aid to cope with the disaster . "
koizumi also said that he would attend a meeting of world leaders to be held in the indonesian capital of jakarta on the 6 th to discuss the issue of aid to countries affected by the tsunamis .
after us president bush was criticized for being slow in response to this great human catastrophe , the us government yesterday increased its promised aid by 10 times to $ 350 million .
china , which has been considered to be more and more interested in challenging japan 's influence in asia , has also promised to provide 60.5 million us dollars in aid , a large number for developing countries .
" japan will mobilize helicopters and personnel from the fire services department to make more contributions , " koizumi said .
japan will also consider making more efforts as soon as possible , including the use of aircraft , warships , and personnel of the japanese self-defense force . "
japan originally promised to provide 30 million us dollars in aid to countries affected by the tsunamis .
a foreign ministry spokesman said that koizumi 's 500 million us dollars also included the 30 million us dollars .
who : 50 groups to provide medical aid to indonesia
the world health organization ( who ) said today that 50 aid groups have arrived in aceh province to provide medical assistance to survivors of the tsunamis .
the world health organization ( who ) is trying to coordinate all organizations and has held a meeting with them this afternoon .
he said that the coordination work is very difficult because many groups have been directly involved in the disaster relief work in aceh .
" we are trying to find out what is going on . every group has just arrived , but every group also indicated that they are very willing to cooperate , " he said in a telephone interview in jakarta .
he reiterated that the world health organization 's main concern is to prevent the outbreak of infectious diseases such as cholera and dysentery , which may cause tens of thousands of deaths .
" we are very worried that many of us are homeless , and they do not have adequate clean drinking water or appropriate food , " he said .
therefore , the conditions for the outbreak of infectious diseases are already in place . "
however , he stressed that there is no sign of the disease so far .
the indonesian ministry of health said that the death toll in the tsunamis might be as high as 100,000 people , most of whom were in aceh province .
since most of the medical facilities in aceh province have been destroyed , in the past week , the indonesian military and the government of singapore and australia have set up at least eight field hospitals , and the un children 's fund has also started to send basic medical bags to help 200,000 children .
