behind - the - scenes political struggle to help tsunami disaster
at a time when the source of materials for the relief of the asian tsunami disaster was flowing into the disaster - stricken areas , a relatively unusual activity was also being carried out in secret : the governments of all countries should provide funds for that , on the one hand , they should receive assistance , and on the other hand , they should play a leading role in this modern largest relief operation .
the catastrophe , which has caused nearly 150,000 people to die , has triggered the old flames of war , including the discord between the united states , the united nations and europe , and the struggle for the leading position in asia .
however , disaster relief experts still have a cautious hope and believe that this tsunami attack on too many countries may lead to a precedent : the countries that promise to provide aid will truly fulfill their commitments .
" the aid commitments made by the governments of various countries have never been carried out in a timely manner , " said zhu ma , professor of international development at the harvard government college .
the aid guaranteed by the governments of various countries has reached as high as $ 2 billion , including un secretary general annan , us secretary of state colin powell , and leaders of australia , china , and japan will hold a political crisis summit in jakarta on the 6 th .
us president bush has increased us aid to nearly 10 times , increasing to us $ 350 million , after being accused of being slow in response and un high - ranking official for relief affairs evans openly criticized the rich countries for being " stingy . "
in asia , the hidden influence of the tsunami disaster on the region has become increasingly confident that china has promised to provide 60.5 million us dollars in aid to a developing country .
japan , which has reduced its foreign aid budget for six years in a row , has also quickly smashed the argument that its national strength is declining with action , and promised to provide at least $ 500 million in aid , which makes all other countries in the world .
