the british weekly " nature " reported that the high - toxic rocket fuel emitted by russia during the launch of the spacecraft at the baikono space base in kazakhstan has caused serious illness to children in the vicinity , but the russian space agency denied this today .
the scientific journal " nature " published today quoted a study as saying that the level of contamination of residents in the region is two times that of common areas .
the study was carried out by a group of russian scientists led by an epidemic expert , the russian president said .
the russian space agency responded by saying : " space - related activities have a direct impact on residents ' health and have not been confirmed . "
the study quoted by the natural science magazine is mainly to study the children of the altai republic .
the republic of altai is located at the crossroads of siberia .
the republic of altai has been selected as a research target because of the pollution of unburned fuel , especially the pollution of the joint venture .
some of russia 's space launch missions are used as fuel for the first few stages .
between 1998 and 2000 , the health records of about 1,000 children in the two polluting areas were compared to those of the nearby unpolluted control teams of 3,300 children .
the number of children in the most polluted areas who need medical care is nearly two times that of the unpolluted group , and the time of treatment is twice as much , the natural science journal reported .
