us trade deficit hits record high in november
us exports shrank by 2.3 percent in november last year , resulting in a record trade deficit of 60.3 billion us dollars , the us commerce department reported today .
us exports dropped to a new low of $ 95.6 billion in the past five months , and at the same time , because us oil import orders increased to $ 14.2 billion , increasing by more than $ 2 billion , and the growth rate reached 1.3 percent , thus increasing imports by 1.3 percent , reaching a record high of $ 155.8 billion .
the trade surplus increased 7.7 percent from the revised $ 56 billion in october last year , and also increased by 50.8 percent from $ 40 billion in november last year .
according to a survey conducted by the company 's market observation , wall street economists predict that the trade deficit of financial goods and labor services will shrink to about 53.3 billion us dollars .
although the us dollar is weak and the products produced by the united states are relatively cheap at home and abroad , the us trade deficit is still expanding .
the commerce department 's report today will put pressure on the us dollar , and again calls on washington to do something in the area of us energy independence and the elimination of us - china trade imbalance .
the decline in us exports in november last year was due to a decrease of 1.4 billion us dollars in capital and financial exports , including a decrease of 325 million us dollars in the export of aircraft and aircraft engines .
exports of industrial materials decreased by 800 million us dollars , with energy being the main source .
exports of motor vehicles , consumer goods , and food also declined .
