china 's largest seawater desalination project settled in zhoushan
xinhua news agency , hangzhou , december 6 ( pan yifeng and xu qun ) the seawater desalination project , the largest of its kind in mainland china , with a daily handling capacity of 10,000 tons , will be settled in the putuo district of zhoushan city , zhejiang province .
for those residents who have suffered from water shortage , the vast and mighty sea water around them for thousands of years will soon become clear and sweet water flowing into every household .
this reporter learned from the relevant departments that the hangzhou water treatment and development center of the state oceanic administration ( soa ) and the government of the liwang town in the putuo district of the zhoushan city recently signed an agreement on the cooperation of 10,000 tons of seawater desalination project .
the first phase of the project is expected to be completed next year , with an investment of 50 million yuan and a daily output of 10,000 tons of fresh water .
the city is one of china 's cities with a relatively serious water shortage .
the city has a total of 1,390 large and small islands , with per capita fresh water possession of 601 cubic meters , only 25.4 percent of zhejiang province 's per capita possession , and the problem of drinking water has all along disturbed the livelihood of the residents of this island city .
for example , the xiangwang town in the putuo district has to transport 1,500 tons of fresh water from a nearby town every day , with a cost of more than 10 yuan per ton .
the anti - infiltration seawater desalination technology developed by the hangzhou water treatment and development center of the state oceanic administration is a process of separation with pressure as a driving force , and is a hot point in the field of international seawater desalination research today .
a relevant person in charge of the center said that the cost of the anti - infiltration seawater desalination project and the consumption of energy have been reduced through technological improvement and the transformation of equipment domestically .
the cost of water desalination per ton has been further reduced on the basis of five yuan .
this indicates that the cost of seawater desalination is likely to be close to the price of tap water and industrial water .
( international ) hungarian referendum results invalid on 5 th
xinhua news agency , budapest , december 5 ( reporter liu min ) - hungary on the 5 th held a referendum on the privatization of national public health medical institutions and the dual nationality of the hungarian people outside the border .
because the number of voters participating in the voting and the number of people who voted for or opposed the two issues did not reach the legal percentage , the result of the voting was invalid .
a total of 30.11 million people , or 37.48 percent of the total number of voters , took part in the voting , according to the results of the country 's national election office .
among them , 1.919 million people and 10.33 million people voted for and opposed the first issue , accounting for 23.87 percent and 12.85 percent of the total number of voters in the whole country , and 15.18 million and 1426,000 people voted for and opposed the second issue , respectively , accounting for 18.88 percent and 17.75 percent of the total number of voters in the whole country .
according to the relevant law of hungary , the result of the referendum is valid only if the number of voters participating in the voting exceeds 50 percent of the total number of voters in the country , or the number of people who voted for or opposed the above - mentioned issue exceeds 25 percent of the total number of voters in the country .
before that , the hungarian government and the ruling party had always called on voters to vote against the two issues , while the opposition parties called on the voters to vote for the two issues .
it is reported that this is the lowest percentage of voters participating in the previous national referendum and elections .
after the result of the vote was announced , hungarian prime minister zorcharani made a speech acknowledging the failure of the referendum .
he said that the government will more actively formulate policies on nationalities and carry out medical and health reforms .
the biggest opposition party in hungary , the president of the youth league , the christian democratic league , said that although the number of people who voted for the vote did not reach the set percentage , this referendum was beneficial .
he called on the government and congress to consider the outcome of the national referendum when formulating relevant laws .
