( international ) china 's scientific expedition team to reach the highest point of antarctic ice cap
xinhua news agency , urumqi , january 8 ( reporter cao yu and shen an ) - zhang zhanhai , head of china 's 21st antarctic scientific expedition team , said on the 8 th that the chinese scientific expedition team has overcome many difficulties and reached the highest level of 50 kilometers from the antarctic inland ice cap , and it is expected that china will be successful in the next two days , thus making china the first country in the world to land in the world , which is called " a country that is not close to the earth . "
zhang zhanhai told xinhua reporters that one of the important objectives of the inspection tour of the " dome - a " is to prepare for the establishment of the third china scientific research station in the hinterland of the antarctic in the future , and to establish a climate environmental monitoring system between the zhongshan station and the " dome - a " .
the team has 13 members , the oldest being 54 , the youngest 26 , and the average age of more than 40 .
seven of them had previously participated in the antarctic inspection , and three of them had participated in the study of high mountains and glaciers in china .
zhang zhanhai said that the ice - covered scientific research was basically carried out according to the plan , but it encountered many difficulties during the period .
the biggest test was that one of the eight snow sals was broken , with the result that the entire team was unable to move forward .
for this reason , all the team members had no choice but to return 60 kilometers , and continued to move forward after the new snow sings were replaced at the headquarters .
another difficulty is altitude reaction .
many members of the team went up to a height of 3,800 meters , and their reaction to the mountain was quite obvious , their breathing was quick , and they had a bad heart reaction .
relying on the spirit of unity and hard work , the scientific research team members overcame numerous difficulties on their way forward .
